I'm feeling pretty riled up right now, so I'm going to speak my mind. 
One - Matt asked for feedback, I gave feedback. I see *no* problem with that.
Two - I'm not going to direct this at anyone, but it always feels like I'm often scapegoated as the one that never washes or cleans up etc. yet everyone is pretty bad at it. Multiple times I've done full-house deep cleans, indiscriminately cleaning whatever. If I need to use something that hasn't been washed up, I just wash it up, I don't hunt down the person that last used it and make them do it for me. I'm not saying it isn't their responsibility, it just often makes more sense to just give it a quick wipe. Moreover, sure, I leave stuff out sometimes - not gonna deny that. But so does *literally everyone*. Baking trays full of grease, bowls full of milk, used plates, cutlery & glasses... It isn't just me, but it's often attributed to me. 
Three - finally, I get that it's easy to be dragged into being petty but I don't get the point of it. If someone asks me to wash something up, I do it. I see literally no problem with that. I don't sit here bitching at everyone else for not doing it, and to be honest, I expect the same in return 😂 Being petty solves fuck all.
